[{"location":"gallery/#Supported-Lattices","page":"Gallery","title":"Supported Lattices","text":"Lattices.jl provides lattices showed below. In each figure, left side shows lattice shape, and right side shows definition of unit cells.  ","category":"section"},{"location":"gallery/#Square-lattice","page":"Gallery","title":"Square lattice","text":"The most fundamental 2D bipartite lattice with coordination number z=4. It has a single site per unit cell and does not exhibit geometric frustration. Often used as a standard benchmark for 2D quantum many-body algorithms. (Image: Square Lattice)","category":"section"},{"location":"gallery/#Triangular-lattice","page":"Gallery","title":"Triangular lattice","text":"A lattice consisting of equilateral triangles with coordination number z=6. It is a prototypical example of a geometrically frustrated lattice (non-bipartite), famous for the 120^circ magnetic order in the Heisenberg model. (Image: Triangular Lattice)","category":"section"},{"location":"gallery/#Honeycomb-lattice","page":"Gallery","title":"Honeycomb lattice","text":"A hexagonal lattice structure found in Graphene. It is a bipartite lattice with coordination number z=3 and contains 2 sites (sublattices A and B) in the unit cell. (Image: Honeycomb Lattice)","category":"section"},{"location":"gallery/#Kagome-lattice","page":"Gallery","title":"Kagome lattice","text":"A lattice consisting of corner-sharing triangles with coordination number z=4. It contains 3 sites in the unit cell. Known for strong geometric frustration and as a candidate host for Quantum Spin Liquids (QSL). (Image: Kagome Lattice)","category":"section"},{"location":"gallery/#Lieb-lattice","page":"Gallery","title":"Lieb lattice","text":"A lattice formed by removing the center sites from a 2 times 2 cluster of the square lattice, or decorating the edges of a square lattice. It is a bipartite lattice characterized by a flat band in its energy spectrum and ferrimagnetic ground states (Lieb's theorem). (Image: Lieb Lattice)","category":"section"},{"location":"gallery/#Shastry-Sutherland-lattice","page":"Gallery","title":"Shastry-Sutherland lattice","text":"A square lattice with additional orthogonal diagonal bonds (dimers). It is geometrically frustrated and realized in the material textSrCu_2(textBO_3)_2. The model is famous for having an exact dimer-singlet ground state in a certain parameter region. (Image: Shastry-Sutherland Lattice)","category":"section"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.jl","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.jl","text":"A Julia package for constructing and visualizing 2D lattices for quantum many-body physics simulations.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"Lattice2D\")","category":"section"},{"location":"#Models","page":"Home","title":"Models","text":"The models implemented in this module is below.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.AbstractBoundaryCondition","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.AbstractBoundaryCondition","text":"AbstractBoundaryCondition\n\n格子の境界条件の抽象型。\n\nPBC: 周期境界条件\nOBC: 開境界条件\nSSD: Sine-Square Deformation 境界条件\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.AbstractLattice","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.AbstractLattice","text":"AbstractLattice{D}\n\n格子の抽象型。Dは空間次元。 ising model などの格子モデルはこの型を継承して実装する。\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.AbstractLatticeConnection","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.AbstractLatticeConnection","text":"AbstractLatticeConnection\n\n格子の接続（辺、ボンド）を表す抽象型。\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.AbstractTopology","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.AbstractTopology","text":"AbstractTopology\n\n格子のトポロジーの抽象型。\n\nSquare: 正方格子\nTriangular: 三角格子\nHoneycomb: ハニカム格子\nKagome: カゴメ格子\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.Bond","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.Bond","text":"Bond\n\n格子の辺を表す型。\n\nsrc::Int: 辺の始点サイトのインデックス\ndst::Int: 辺の終点サイトのインデックス\ntype::Int: 辺の種類（異なる結合定数を持つ辺を区別するため）\nvector::Vector{Float64}: 辺のベクトル表現\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.Connection","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.Connection","text":"Connection\n\n単位胞内または単位胞間の接続ルール。\n\nsrc_sub: 始点のサブ格子インデックス (1, 2, ...)\ndst_sub: 終点のサブ格子インデックス\ndx, dy: 終点がどの相対セルにあるか (0,0 なら同じ単位胞内)\ntype: 結合の種類\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.Honeycomb","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.Honeycomb","text":"Honeycomb <: AbstractTopology{2}\n\nstruct which represents Honeycomb lattice\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.Kagome","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.Kagome","text":"Kagome <: AbstractTopology{2}\n\nstruct which represents Kagome lattice\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.Lattice2D","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.Lattice2D","text":"Lattice2D{Topology<:AbstractTopology, T, B<:AbstractBoundaryCondition} 2次元格子を表す型。\n\nLx::Int: x方向の格子サイズ\nLy::Int: y方向の格子サイズ\nN::Int: サイト総数\npositions::Vector{Vector{T}}: 各サイトの位置ベクトル\nnearest_neighbors::Vector{Vector{Int}}: 各サイトの最近接サイトのインデックスリスト\nbonds::Vector{Bond}: 格子の辺のリスト\nbasis_vectors::Vector{Vector{T}}: 格子の基底ベクトル\nreciprocal_vectors::Union{Vector{Vector{T}}, Nothing}: 逆格子ベクトル\nsublattice_ids::Vector{Int}: 各サイトのサブ格子ID\nis_bipartite::Bool: 格子が二部グラフかどうか\nsite_map::Union{Matrix{Int}, Nothing}: 格子上のサイトインデックスのマッピング\ntranslation_x::Vector{Int}: x方向の平行移動ベクトル\ntranslation_y::Vector{Int}: y方向の平行移動ベクトル\nboundary::B: 境界条件\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.Lieb","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.Lieb","text":"Lieb <: AbstractTopology{2}\n\nstruct which represents Lieb lattice\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.ShastrySutherland","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.ShastrySutherland","text":"ShastrySutherland <: AbstractTopology{2}\n\nstruct which represents Shastry-Sutherland lattice\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.Square","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.Square","text":"Square <: AbstractTopology{2}\n\nstruct which represents Square lattice\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.Triangular","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.Triangular","text":"Triangular <: AbstractTopology{2}\n\nstruct which represents Triangular lattice\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.UnitCell","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.UnitCell","text":"UnitCell{D, T}\n\n格子の幾何学的定義データ。基本的に、この情報をもとに格子を構築する。 get_unit_cell(::Type{T}) 関数で各トポロジーに対応する単位胞データを取得する。\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.build_lattice-Tuple{Type{<:Lattice2D.AbstractTopology}, Int64, Int64}","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.build_lattice","text":"build_lattice(Topology::Type{<:AbstractTopology}, Lx::Int, Ly::Int; boundary::AbstractBoundaryCondition=PBC())\n\nConstruct a lattice with the specified topology, size, and boundary conditions. this function is available if unitcell information is defined.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.calc_reciprocal_vectors-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.calc_reciprocal_vectors","text":"calc_reciprocal_vectors(basis)\n\nCalculate reciprocal lattice vectors from the given basis vectors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.check_bipartite_bfs-Tuple{Int64, Vector{Vector{Int64}}}","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.check_bipartite_bfs","text":"check_bipartite_bfs(N, neighbors)\n\ncheck whether the given lattice is bipartite using BFS.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#Lattice2D.get_unit_cell-Union{Tuple{Type{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T<:Lattice2D.AbstractTopology","page":"Home","title":"Lattice2D.get_unit_cell","text":"get_unit_cell(::Type{T}) where T <: AbstractTopology\n\nthis function returns the UnitCell associated with the given Topology type. If the Topology type is not recognized, it throws an error.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
